checkBalance(address).details: Get the total asset value held in the platform

returns.balance: Total amount of the asset in the platform

checkInterestEarned(address).details: Get the amount of asset/collateral earned as interest

returns._0: interestEarned The amount of asset/collateral earned as interest

checkRewardEarned().details: Get the amount of asset/collateral earned as interest

returns._0: interestEarned The amount of asset/collateral earned as interest

params._asset: Asset type deposited into this strategy contract

collectRewardToken().details: Collect accumulated CRV and send to Vault.

initialize(address,address,address,addre.notice: Initializer for setting up strategy internal state. This overrides the InitializableAbstractStrategy initializer as Curve strategies don't fit well within that abstraction.

params._assets: Addresses of supported assets. MUST be passed in the same                order as returned by coins on the pool contract

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removePToken(uint256).details: Remove a supported asset by passing its index.      This method can only be called by the system owner

params._assetIndex: Index of the asset to be removed

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

safeApproveAllTokens().details: Approve the spending of all assets by their corresponding pool tokens,      if for some reason is it necessary.

setPTokenAddress(address,address).details: Provide support for asset by passing its pToken address.      This method can only be called by the system owner

params._pToken: Address for the corresponding platform token

supportsCollateral(address).details: Check if an asset/collateral is supported.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw(address,address,uint256).details: Withdraw an amount of asset from the platform.

params._recipient: Address to which the asset should be sent
